  "output": "# Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\nNo test suite exists (`find` turned up zero project tests; only the `.venv`'s own vendored tests). All 1,809 lines across 7 modules (`models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `pipeline.py`, `notify.py`, `fetchers.py`, `agent.py`) are currently uncovered. Below is the gap analysis by module, with skeletons for each. Recommend adding `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, and `respx` (for mocking `httpx` — the fetchers docstring already says the client is \"injectable so parsing logic is unit-testable against mocked transports\") as dev dependencies; none are currently in `requirements.txt` or the venv.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py` — untested entirely\n\n**Gaps:** `parse_posted_at`'s three branches (epoch ms/s, ISO, unparseable), the ms/s boundary at `1e12`, `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash` change-detection semantics, `Job.to_row` field shape.\n\n```python\n# test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds_lever_style(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_ms_vs_seconds_boundary(self):\n        # exactly 1e12 must be treated as ms; 1e12 - 1 as seconds\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"999999999999\").year > 30000  # seconds interpretation, far future\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"1000000000000\").year == 2001  # ms interpretation\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt == datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 0, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_assumed_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_unparseable_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_epoch_string(self):\n        # lstrip(\"-\").isdigit() accepts \"-123\"; document actual behavior\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"-100\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not a date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        base.update(kw)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_identity(self):\n        j = self._job()\n        assert j.key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_change(self):\n        a = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        b = self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert a.content_hash != b.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_when_salary_changes(self):\n        # content_hash only hashes title/location/url/department\n        a = self._job(salary_range=\"100k\")\n        b = self._job(salary_range=\"200k\")\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_adds_key_and_hash(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n\n    def test_posted_dt_delegates_to_parse_posted_at(self):\n        j = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert j.posted_dt.year == 2024\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filters.py` — untested entirely\n\n**Gaps:** word-boundary regex behavior (substring vs whole-word), exclude-precedence-over-include, unparseable-date-is-kept policy, `filter_jobs` default handling of missing rule keys.\n\n```python\n# test_filters.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef make_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\", department=\"\", location=\"Remote\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=title, url=\"u\", department=department, location=location,\n                posted_at=posted_at)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_include_keyword_word_boundary_not_substring(self):\n        # \"eng\" shouldn't match \"engineering\" — \\b enforces whole words\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Eng Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_takes_precedence_over_include(self):\n        j = make_job(title=\"Senior Staff Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"senior\"]) is False\n\n    def test_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"ENGINEER\"), include=[\"engineer\"]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_substring_match(self):\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"Austin, TX\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_confirmed_date(self):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(make_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_date(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(make_job(posted_at=\"Posted recently\"), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_no_filters_passes_everything(self):\n        assert match(make_job()) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_dict_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(), make_job(title=\"Other\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_computes_cutoff(self):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n        jobs = [make_job(posted_at=old)]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": 5}) == []\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_string(self):\n        # rules.get(\"max_age_days\") cast via float(); confirm string input works\n        jobs = [make_job(posted_at=\"\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": \"5\"}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `store.py` — untested entirely (highest-risk gap: dedup correctness is the whole point of the app)\n\n**Gaps:** new-vs-changed-vs-unchanged classification, legacy-column migration, `next_seq` monotonicity/concurrency, `added_since` ordering and strict-`>` boundary, context-manager close.\n\n```python\n# test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport threading\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef make_job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=external_id,\n               title=title, url=\"u\", **kw)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_reported_and_inserted(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither_new_nor_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_changed_content_reported_as_changed_not_new(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(title=\"Engineer I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([make_job(title=\"Engineer II\")])\n        assert new == []\n        assert len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_last_seen_updates_even_when_unchanged(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen, last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert row[\"first_seen\"] <= row[\"last_seen\"]\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self, store):\n        assert store.diff([]) == ([], [])\n\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_legacy_db_missing_salary_range_gets_column_added(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(path))\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n            CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        s = Store(path)  # should not raise\n        s.diff([make_job(salary_range=\"100k\")])\n        s.close()\n\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\n    def test_set_meta_then_get(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v1\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_upserts_on_conflict(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_starts_at_one_and_increments(self, store):\n        assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 1\n        assert store.next_seq(\"counter\") == 2\n\n    def test_independent_counters(self, store):\n        store.next_seq(\"a\")\n        assert store.next_seq(\"b\") == 1\n\n    def test_concurrent_claims_are_unique(self, tmp_path):\n        # BEGIN IMMEDIATE should serialize concurrent claimers, not race\n        path = tmp_path / \"concurrent.db\"\n        results = []\n        def claim():\n            with Store(path) as s:\n                results.append(s.next_seq(\"report_seq\"))\n        threads = [threading.Thread(target=claim) for _ in range(10)]\n        for t in threads: t.start()\n        for t in threads: t.join()\n        assert sorted(results) == list(range(1, 11))\n\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_strictly_greater_than_excludes_equal_timestamp(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n\n    def test_ordered_by_first_seen_company_title(self, store):\n        store.diff([make_job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"B\", company=\"acme\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00\")\n        assert len(rows) == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `pipeline.py` — untested entirely\n\n**Gaps:** `load_config` default injection for each missing key, `dry_run` short-circuit (no store touched, no dispatch), the full happy-path wiring.\n\n```python\n# test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\ndef test_load_config_fills_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\ndef test_load_config_preserves_explicit_values(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\nconcurrency: 3\\ndb: custom.db\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 3\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"custom.db\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_does_not_touch_store_or_dispatch(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: [{ats: greenhouse, company: acme}]\\n\")\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as MockStore, \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    MockStore.assert_not_called()\n    mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_diffs_and_dispatches(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path)\n    mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n    assert set(result) == {\"matched\", \"new\", \"changed\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `notify.py` — untested entirely (error-isolation behavior in `dispatch` is the most important gap)\n\n**Gaps:** env-var-gated no-op branches for every notifier, `_sms_body` truncation math, and — critically — that `dispatch` isolates one notifier's exception from the rest.\n\n```python\n# test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef make_job(title=\"Engineer\", company=\"acme\", salary_range=\"\", location=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=company, external_id=\"1\",\n               title=title, url=\"https://x\", location=location, salary_range=salary_range)\n\nclass TestNotifyConsole:\n    def test_no_jobs_prints_none_message(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([], [])\n        assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    def test_new_and_changed_both_printed(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([make_job(title=\"New\")], [make_job(title=\"Changed\")])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"NEW listing\" in out and \"UPDATED listing\" in out\n\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_without_env_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([make_job()], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_noop_when_no_jobs_even_with_url(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_posts_formatted_blocks(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack/x\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_slack([make_job(salary_range=\"100k\")], [])\n        payload = post.call_args.kwargs[\"json\"]\n        assert \"100k\" in payload[\"text\"]\n\n\nclass TestNotifyEmail:\n    def test_noop_without_smtp_host_or_to(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"notify.smtplib.SMTP\") as smtp:\n            notify.notify_email([make_job()], [])\n        smtp.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_login_only_when_smtp_user_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", \"smtp.x\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"EMAIL_TO\", \"a@b.com\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SMTP_USER\", raising=False)\n        mock_conn = MagicMock()\n        with patch(\"notify.smtplib.SMTP\") as smtp:\n            smtp.return_value.__enter__.return_value = mock_conn\n            notify.notify_email([make_job()], [])\n        mock_conn.login.assert_not_called()\n\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_and_appends_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [make_job(title=f\"Job{i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n        assert body.count(\"- Job\") == 8\n\n    def test_ascii_only_no_bullets_or_ellipsis(self):\n        body = notify._sms_body([make_job()], [])\n        assert \"•\" not in body and \"…\" not in body\n\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_noop_when_any_of_four_env_vars_missing(self, monkeypatch):\n        for var in (\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"TWILIO_FROM\", \"TWILIO_TO\"):\n            monkeypatch.delenv(var, raising=False)\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            notify.notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n        post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_response(self, monkeypatch):\n        for var, val in [(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\"), (\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\"),\n                          (\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\"), (\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")]:\n            monkeypatch.setenv(var, val)\n        with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n            post.return_value.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"bad creds\")\n            with pytest.raises(Exception):\n                notify.notify_sms([make_job()], [])\n\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failure_does_not_block_others(self, capsys):\n        # missing error-isolation test: dispatch wraps each notifier in try/except\n        failing = MagicMock(side_effect=RuntimeError(\"boom\"), __name__=\"failing\")\n        succeeding = MagicMock(__name__=\"succeeding\")\n        with patch(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [failing, succeeding]):\n            notify.dispatch([make_job()], [])\n        succeeding.assert_called_once()\n        assert \"failing failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. `fetchers.py` — untested entirely, largest and highest-risk surface\n\nThis file is explicitly designed to be unit-testable with injected transports (per its own docstring) — that design intent is currently unexercised. Group by concern:\n\n### 6a. Retry/backoff core (`_request`) — most important untested logic\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_request.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_succeeds_on_first_try():\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n    transport = httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport) as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x/y\")\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(503)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=4)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error():\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(500)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_non_retryable_404_is_still_retried_then_raises():\n    # documents current behavior: raise_for_status() also raises HTTPStatusError,\n    # which is caught by the same except clause as the retryable branch —\n    # a 404 gets retried `retries` times before failing, not fast-failed.\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=3)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_transport_error_retried():\n    def handler(request):\n        raise httpx.ConnectError(\"refused\")\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x/y\", retries=2)\n```\n\n### 6b. Simple JSON parsers — one representative skeleton per parser (currently zero exist)\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n                       _ashby_salary, parse_smartrecruiters, parse_recruitee,\n                       parse_workable)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_basic_fields_mapped(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"Remote\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}], \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01\"}]}\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"Remote\"\n        assert jobs[0].department == \"Eng\"\n\n    def test_missing_optional_fields_do_not_crash(self):\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1}]})\n        assert jobs[0].title == \"\" and jobs[0].location == \"\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_jobs_key(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {}) == []\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_range_with_currency(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}) \\\n            == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description_plain(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_filtered_out(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}, {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True}]}\n        jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", data)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].external_id == \"2\"\n\n\nclass TestParseRecruitee:\n    def test_location_falls_back_to_city_country(self):\n        data = {\"offers\": [{\"id\": 1, \"city\": \"Berlin\", \"country\": \"Germany\"}]}\n        assert parse_recruitee(\"acme\", data)[0].location == \"Berlin, Germany\"\n\n\nclass TestParseWorkable:\n    def test_dict_location_prefers_location_str(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"shortcode\": \"abc\", \"location\": {\"location_str\": \"NYC\"}}]}\n        assert parse_workable(\"acme\", data)[0].location == \"NYC\"\n\n    def test_missing_location_falls_back_to_city_state_country(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"city\": \"Austin\", \"state\": \"TX\", \"country\": \"US\"}]}\n        assert parse_workable(\"acme\", data)[0].location == \"Austin, TX, US\"\n```\n\n### 6c. Bespoke scrapers — regex/HTML fragility is the risk here (Google, D.E. Shaw, Two Sigma, Apple, ByteDance)\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_bespoke.py\nfrom fetchers import (_extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_google, parse_deshaw,\n                       parse_twosigma, _apple_hydration, _apple_posted_at,\n                       _bd_location, parse_bytedance, _amazon_posted_at)\n\nclass TestGoogleDs1:\n    def test_extract_ds1_missing_marker_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json] , sideChannel\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_time_index_12(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000]\n        job[13] = [1800000000]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n        # index 12 timestamp should win over index 13\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_short_list_no_crash(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([1, 2]) == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_first_element(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [[None, \"title\"]]) == []\n\n\nclass TestParseDeshaw:\n    def test_dedups_repeated_job_id(self):\n        page = ('data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span>'\n                'data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span>')\n        assert len(parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)) == 1\n\n    def test_missing_location_defaults_empty(self):\n        page = 'data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">A</span>'\n        assert parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)[0].location == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseTwosigma:\n    def test_triple_rendered_role_deduped(self):\n        anchor = ('href=\"https://careers.twosigma.com/careers/JobDetail/x/123\"> Role </a>'\n                   ) * 3\n        assert len(parse_twosigma(\"twosigma\", anchor)) == 1\n\n\nclass TestAppleHydration:\n    def test_handles_escaped_quotes_in_json_string(self):\n        html = 'window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"{\\\\\"a\\\\\":1}\")'\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) == {\"a\": 1}\n\n    def test_missing_marker_returns_none(self):\n        assert _apple_hydration(\"<html></html>\") is None\n\n    def test_apple_posted_at_trims_nanoseconds_to_microseconds(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668311Z\") == \\\n            \"2024-01-15T10:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\n    def test_apple_posted_at_empty_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestBdLocation:\n    def test_walks_parent_chain_city_state_country(self):\n        city = {\"en_name\": \"SF\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"CA\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"US\"}}}\n        assert _bd_location(city) == \"SF, CA, US\"\n\n    def test_none_input_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Xyzember 1, 2024\") == \"\"\n```\n\n### 6d. Pagination fetchers (async, need `httpx.MockTransport`) — dedup-across-pages and stop-conditions untested\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_pagination.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_optiver, fetch_microsoft, fetch_workday, fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_optiver_stops_when_page_returns_nothing_new():\n    pages = [\n        {\"items\": [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/a\", \"title\": \"A\"}]},\n        {\"items\": []},\n    ]\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        resp = pages[min(calls[\"n\"], len(pages) - 1)]\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(200, json=resp)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_optiver(client, {\"company\": \"optiver\", \"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_at_total_and_safety_cap():\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 0})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"x.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com\",\n                                             \"tenant\": \"x\", \"site\": \"Site\"})\n    assert jobs == []\n\n\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"not-a-real-ats\"})\n\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_one_source_failure_does_not_abort_others(self):\n        # per-source try/except in fetch_all.one() — currently unexercised\n        def handler(request):\n            if \"greenhouse\" in str(request.url):\n                return httpx.Response(500)\n            return httpx.Response(200, json=[])\n        transport = httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=transport)\n        sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"fails\"},\n                   {\"ats\": \"lever\", \"company\": \"works\"}]\n        jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client)\n        await client.aclose()\n        assert jobs == []  # both empty, but no exception propagated\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_does_not_close_injected_client(self):\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n        await fetch_all([], client=client)\n        assert not client.is_closed\n        await client.aclose()\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_closes_owned_client(self):\n        # owns_client path — no client passed in\n        jobs = await fetch_all([])\n        assert jobs == []\n```\n\n### 6e. Meta's GraphQL scraping — token extraction, `for (;;);` stripping, error surfacing (currently a stated maintenance hazard — see memory `meta-jd-fetch`/`meta-careers-fetcher`)\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_meta.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_meta\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_meta_strips_for_loop_prefix_and_parses(monkeypatch):\n    page_html = '[\"LSD\",[],{\"token\":\"abc123\"}]  \"__spin_r\":42 \"__spin_b\":\"b\" \"__spin_t\":1'\n    graphql_body = 'for (;;);{\"data\":{\"job_search_with_featured_jobs_v2\":{\"all_jobs\":[{\"id\":\"1\",\"title\":\"SWE\",\"locations\":[\"Remote\"],\"teams\":[\"Eng\"]}]}}}'\n    def handler(request):\n        if request.url.path == \"/jobs\":\n            return httpx.Response(200, text=page_html)\n        return httpx.Response(200, text=graphql_body)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler),\n                                  base_url=\"https://www.metacareers.com\") as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].external_id == \"1\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_meta_raises_on_graphql_errors(monkeypatch):\n    def handler(request):\n        if request.url.path == \"/jobs\":\n            return httpx.Response(200, text=\"\")\n        return httpx.Response(200, text='{\"errors\":[{\"message\":\"doc_id rotated\"}]}')\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler),\n                                  base_url=\"https://www.metacareers.com\") as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"doc_id rotated\"):\n            await fetch_meta(client, {\"company\": \"meta\"})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. `agent.py` — untested entirely (CLI/DB glue + PDF pipeline)\n\n**Gaps:** `cmd_db_new`'s first-run window, watermark truncation logic (group-boundary truncation, not row-level), `--posted-days`/`--dated-only` interactions, `cmd_db_mark` timestamp validation, `_normalize_ats` character replacement table (and that it skips `<style>`/`<script>`/tag content), the mode-word/flag-splitting logic in `main()`.\n\n```python\n# test_agent.py\nimport json, pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_new, cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, main\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef _seed(db_path, n=3):\n    with Store(db_path) as s:\n        # insert rows directly or via store.diff with fabricated Jobs\n        pass\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\"])\n        assert rc == 2\n        assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n    def test_requires_watermark_or_now(self, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_time(self, tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        assert rc == 0\n\n\nclass TestDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n        rc = cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"3\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n\n    def test_dated_only_drops_undated_rows(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        # requires seeding store with a mix of dated/undated jobs first\n        pass\n\n    def test_truncation_respects_first_seen_group_boundaries(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        # a group of N rows sharing first_seen must not be split mid-group\n        # even if it pushes the result past --limit\n        pass\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_smart_quotes_and_dashes(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201CHello\\u201D \\u2014 world\\u2026</p>\")\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in html and \"- world...\" in html\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n    def test_skips_style_and_script_blocks(self):\n        html_in = \"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n        html_out, counts = _normalize_ats(html_in)\n        assert \"content: '\\u2014';\" in html_out  # untouched inside <style>\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n    def test_skips_tag_attributes(self):\n        html_in = '<a title=\"\\u2014\">\\u2014</a>'\n        html_out, counts = _normalize_ats(html_in)\n        assert 'title=\"\\u2014\"' in html_out\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\n\nclass TestMainArgParsing:\n    def test_bare_invocation_is_interactive(self, monkeypatch):\n        called = {}\n        monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent.run_claude\", lambda mw, i, e: called.update(mw=mw, i=i, e=e))\n        main.__wrapped__ if hasattr(main, \"__wrapped__\") else None\n        # patch sys.argv and assert run_claude called with interactive=True\n\n    def test_flag_after_mode_words_splits_correctly(self, monkeypatch):\n        # e.g. `agent.py scan --foo bar` -> mode_words=[\"scan\"], extra=[\"--foo\",\"bar\"]\n        pass\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of gaps by category\n\n| Category | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Untested functions/classes | All ~60 public functions/classes across 7 modules |\n| Edge cases | Epoch ms/s boundary, unparseable dates kept-not-dropped, exclude-over-include precedence, dedup across triple-rendered HTML, group-boundary truncation in `db-new`, ms-vs-seconds epoch |\n| Error handling | `dispatch()`'s per-notifier isolation, `_request`'s retry-on-4xx behavior (likely unintended — 404s get retried, not fast-failed), `fetch_all`'s per-source isolation, Meta's `RuntimeError` on rotated `doc_id`, SQLite migration path for legacy DBs |\n| Integration gaps | `pipeline.run()` end-to-end (config → fetch → filter → store → notify) with only fetch/notify mocked; `agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` round trip against a real `Store`; `Store.next_seq` under real concurrency (threaded test above) |\n\nBiggest priority given the app's purpose: **`store.py`'s `diff()`** (new/changed/unchanged classification is the core dedup guarantee) and **`fetchers.py`'s `_request`** (the 404-gets-retried behavior looks like a latent bug worth confirming intent on before writing the test as a lock-in).\n",
